Demolition of 'illegally built' temple in Delhi postponed .
New Delhi, Jul 17 (PTI) The authorities have postponed the demolition of a temple, allegedly built illegally at east Delhis Shahdara, due to "administrative reasons", the police said today. The temple was to be demolished today but the authorities have postponed it to August 21. "We have received a letter from the Public Works Department (PWD) communicating the change of date," said a senior police official. 